examples.en: White Rose
The price of milk rose.
A wind rose.
She rose to the level of manager.
Red Rose
The team rose to the challenge.
He rose to the rank of major.
He rose up and down sat she.
Christ rose from the dead.
His voice rose to a bellow.
examples.ru: Его голос превратился в звериный рёв. / Он уже не говорил, а орал.

examples.en: His voice rose in frustration.
She rose gracefully to her feet.
The tide rose and fell.
examples.ru: Морские волны то поднимались, то опускались.

examples.en: Growl rose from the mob.
examples.ru: Из толпы был слышен недовольный гул.

examples.en: The cliffs rose above them.
She pinned a rose to her dress.
There is no rose without a thorn.
The lights dimmed and the curtain rose.
examples.ru: Свет (в зале) погас, и занавес поднялся.

examples.en: The waves rose and fell.
Smoke rose from the chimney.
Prices rose at a dizzy rate.
The hail got the rose bushes.
The noise rose to a crescendo.
The road gradually rose upward.
The peasants rose in rebellion.
The wind rose in the afternoon.
Wisps of smoke rose into the air.
'I don't understand,' whined Rose.
The audience rose a new performance.
examples.ru: Публика с восторгом приняла новую пьесу.

examples.en: The noise rose to a deafening pitch.
